# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## Unreleased

### Added

- Configuration to use the module as satellite or access point

### Changed

## 1.5.1 - 2025-06-01

### Added

- Configuration documentation.

### Changed

- Update documentation.
- Convert documentation to Markdown format.
- Rename all occurrence of the app to ChronoRootControl.

## 1.5.0 - 2025-05-31

### Added

- Scheduler status in the application config pages.
- User config file to overwrite default info.

### Changed

- Refactor the experiment status in one place.

### Fixed

- Stop an experience if not future picture will be taken.
- Do not load an ended or canceled experienced in the scheduler.
- Some miss-spelling and html bugs.
- Do not display the date of next image if not in scheduler.

### Removed

- Configuration files to run on a laptop.

## 1.4.0 - 2025-05-31

### Added

- Collect the next image time from scheduler.
- Next image time of experiment list page.
- Scheduler status set as an exchanged file in /run.
- Instructions to automatically mount a USB drive.

### Changed

- Homogenize and simplified the experiment status.
- Clean and correct the requirements.txt file.
- Modify default experiment path to /srv/ChronoRootData and default interval to 15 min.
- Do not dump the experiment status file at each picture.
- Transform print statements to logging.
- Color picture if no backlight
- Renaming working folder to ChronoRootControl.
- Update installation procedure from scratch (Bullseye).
- Real gray value pictures if in backlight configuration.

### Fixed

- Table line color according to experiment status.
- Some spelling correction.
- Use the computer time instead of the fixed one from Paris.
- Next image time of experiment description page according to scheduler.
- I2C interface activation.
- Use of IR and camera warm time configuration.
- Multiplexer self check for Bullseye.

